Nyanza deputy county commissioners have been directed to deal firmly with those fuelling political violence.Regional coordinator Wilson Njega on Thursday said the government will not tolerate lawlessness and ordered the administrators to arrest anybody involved in chaos. He said they are committed to having a peaceful environment to allow free and fair elections next year.Njega warned youths against being hired to intimidate and harass people in rallies and funerals. He put on notice outlawed groups such as China Squad and American Marines, which have been terrorising innocent citizens. Those illegal groups must surrender before we catch up with them. They are used by selfish politicians, he said in Kisumu.Njega warned politicians that they will not be spared. We are closely monitoring individuals who sponsor youths to cause animosity, he said. Njega said 21 people have been arraigned in court over chaos-related cases.